.SH NAME
cmat_new_set \- new matrix with a given value
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fB#include <it/mat.h>
.sp
cmat cmat_new_set ( cplx val, int h, int w
);
\fR
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
The function \fBcmat_new_set\fR returns a matrix of size \fIh\fRx\fIw\fR, where \fIh\fR and \fIw\fR are respectively the height and the width of the return matrix. All the elements are set to the parameter value \fIval\fR\&.   
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.PP
The new matrix
.SH "EXAMPLE"

.nf

#include <mat.h>

\&...

cmat m = cmat_new_set (4, 2, 3);   /* m = [[4 4 4]
                                           [4 4 4]  */
.fi
